1. Relevant equations  
The oscillatory amplitude for the $p$-th harmonic (neglecting impurity scattering) is  
$$A_p\propto\frac{1}{p}R_T(p),$$  
with the Lifshitzâ€“Kosevich thermal damping factor  
$$R_T(p)=\frac{X_p}{\sinh(X_p)},\quad X_p=\frac{2\pi^2pk_BT}{\hbar\omega_c}.$$  

2. Express $X_p$ in terms of $X_1$  
Since $X_p=pX_1$, we have  
$$X_1=\frac{2\pi^2k_BT}{\hbar\omega_c},\qquad X_2=2X_1.$$  

3. Write the ratio $A_2/A_1$  
$$\frac{A_2}{A_1}
=\frac{\frac{1}{2}R_T(2)}{\frac{1}{1}R_T(1)}
=\frac{1}{2}\,\frac{R_T(2)}{R_T(1)}.$$

4. Substitute $R_T(1)$ and $R_T(2)$  
$$R_T(1)=\frac{X_1}{\sinh(X_1)},\qquad 
R_T(2)=\frac{2X_1}{\sinh(2X_1)}.$$
Hence
\begin{align*}
\frac{A_2}{A_1}
&=\frac{1}{2}
\frac{\displaystyle \frac{2X_1}{\sinh(2X_1)}}
{\displaystyle \frac{X_1}{\sinh(X_1)}}
=\frac{1}{2}\,\frac{2X_1}{\sinh(2X_1)}\frac{\sinh(X_1)}{X_1}
=\frac{\sinh(X_1)}{\sinh(2X_1)}.
\end{align*}

5. Simplify using $\sinh(2X_1)=2\sinh(X_1)\cosh(X_1)$  
$$\frac{A_2}{A_1}
=\frac{\sinh(X_1)}{2\sinh(X_1)\cosh(X_1)}
=\frac{1}{2\cosh(X_1)}.$$
